text.tspan: 1969 Dicke, the Universe is flat now, but had to be far
The start of the Universe is not stable, it should ball up.
There is no reason matter should move at the same speed.
Inflation - magic! Universe briefly grows like crazy
Don't use Newton out-of-the-box, things are moving
Need a stable, constant velocity solution for gravity.
Product rule may come into play
Use BOTH terms, not just the first one
